the land of Rameses. Following Pharaoh’s orders, Joseph settles his family in Goshen, identified here as the region of Rameses. This phrase appears to be an editorial comment, for this terminology was not used until the thirteenth-century pharaohs of the 19th Dynasty. The region of Rameses (cf. Exod. 1:11; 12:37; Num. 33:3, 5) may be identified with Qantir or Tanis in the northeastern delta of the Nile. It became the residence city of the kings of the 19th Dynasty and was built by and named after Ramses II (1304–1227 b.c.). 

