            <Text>1. with their flocks and herds. Joseph emphasizes that his family are shepherds to assure the Pharaoh that they entertain no social or political ambitions and to preserve them from an alien way of life and intermarriage with the Egyptians (see 34:9). The latter threat was more acute with the possession of property in Egypt (see 47:11). Waltke, B. K., &amp; Fredricks, C. J. (2001). Genesis: a commentary (p. 586). Grand Rapids, MI: Zondervan.

