community of peoples. See 28:3 and note. The promise to Israel is narrowed down to Ephraim in 48:19–20. During the divided monarchy (930–722 b.c.) Ephraim’s descendants, as the most powerful tribe, sometimes gave their name to all the peoples that made up the northern kingdom (e.g., Isa. 7:2, 5, 8–9; Hos. 9:13; 12:1, 8). Waltke, B. K., &amp; Fredricks, C. J. (2001). Genesis: a commentary (p. 596). Grand Rapids, MI: Zondervan.
Promise also found in 35:11-12
